From: SentCom v19.34.28 Patch L2b
Subject: [PATCH] v19.34.28 Patch L2b — Reconciler / Account-Guard wiring through BOT_ORDER_PATH=direct

Completes the IB_DIRECT_MIGRATION_PLAN's L2 phase by wiring the four
read consumers identified in the plan at the ib-direct fast paths
(scaffolded in L2a) when the operator sets BOT_ORDER_PATH=direct:

  1. orphan_gtc_reconciler._fetch_ib_positions -> get_positions_fresh()
  2. position_reconciler.reconcile_positions_with_ib -> get_positions_fresh()
  3. position_reconciler.sync_position_from_ib -> get_positions_fresh()
  4. account_guard lookup in trading_bot_service -> ib_direct.managedAccounts()

Already on ib-direct before L2b (no work needed):
  - cancel_orphan_gtc_orders (uses ib_direct.cancel_order primary)
  - _fetch_ib_open_orders (3-tier resolver with ib_direct as tier 1)
  - naked_position_sweep reissue path (uses attach_oca_stop_target,
    which L2a wired to ib_direct.place_oca_stop_target)

Default BOT_ORDER_PATH=pusher unchanged — all four new branches are
no-ops until the operator flips the env var on Monday per the L3
runbook in IB_DIRECT_MIGRATION_PLAN.md.

Tests: 10 new L2b regressions, 53/53 total green
(Patch J 8 + L1 8 + L2a 27 + L2b 10).

Base: b89fc197 (v19.34.28 Patch L2a)

